<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-827-034  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 827 034.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Oct 30 1989 n272 p59(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fujitsu begins a Texas-size plant. (Fujitsu America Inc buildsplant in Richardson, TX)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Abel, Glenn.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Fujitsu Ltd, the $18 billion Japanese computer, communicationssystems and semiconductor giant, breaks ground on an $80 milliontelecommunications manufacturing facility in Richardson, TX.andP;  TheUS operations of Fujitsu America Inc total $1.4 billion incommunications equipment, cellular phones and switching andtransmission gear.andP;  The factory will employ 4,500 American workersby the year 2000.andP;  Among the telecommunications manufactures atthe new plant will be transmission products and systems, cellularmobile phones, digital cross-connect products and local and longdistance fiber optic transmission gear.andP;  A crucial beta testing ofthe Fujitsu Fetex-150 digital switch system, now under way atAtlanta's Southern Bell Telephone and Telegraph Co, will determinewhether or not Fujitsu manufactures the digital switch at its newfacility.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Fujitsu Ltd. (planning)Fujitsu America Inc. (location).andO;Product:   Fujitsu FETEX-150 (Telecommunication switching system)(marketing).andO;Topic:     Communications EquipmentStrategic PlanningFacility LocationProductsTexasForeign InvestmentBeta Testing.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   At a glance: Fujitsu Ltd, Tokyo. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>